{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"90de6c7b-fafc-4e8f-adb6-baa3b6cc98f5","content":"Yes, you'll run into compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 drops support for older target frameworks.** Specifically:\n\n- **`net462`** — MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework **4.7.2** (`net472`).\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — MSTest v3 requires at minimum **.NET 6.0** (`net6.0`).\n- **`net5.0`** — Also unsupported; .NET 5 is out of support and MSTest v3 targets `net6.0`+.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to something like:**\n\n```\nnet6.0;net472\n```\n\n(or `net8.0;net472` depending on your needs)\n\nIf you must continue testing against those older frameworks, you'll need to stay on MSTest v2 for those targets or split your test project.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"316b1936-8e61-4dc2-8f99-b7252cc61fc5","outputTokens":217,"requestId":"BC28:26D998:2170EF5:253D46A:69FAA836"},"id":"1d208e2e-f544-4757-b17e-97f57844d529","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:32:29.568Z","parentId":"358b53b7-9eea-40c8-b71e-7eda6d664b8a"}
